The Vice President, Mike Pence, spoke at Fort Drum in New York, praising President Donald Trump for his commitment to strengthening the military. Pence highlighted Trump's actions to increase military spending, defeat ISIS, secure commitments from NATO allies, and prioritize American dominance in land, sea, air, and space. He also mentioned Trump's signing of legislation to rebuild the military and bring home missing soldiers. Pence assured the audience that the administration will continue to support and fight for the armed forces. The event concluded with Pence introducing President Trump as a champion of the military.